rComments: Carra is a little shy and quiet, but her passion for poetry shows. She is so dedicated, and enjoys hearing students' ideas and opinions. She incorporates unconventional materials into the class and shows you new ways to view the same old stuff. Plus she's adorable in her combat boots and skirts.

I felt like I was falling in love with Carra towards the beginning of the class..(maybe also because I love 20th cent. American poetry) but towards the end of the class, it seemed she ran out of things to say. Very dedicated though, and the nicest person you will ever meet. plus, she is extremely sexy.

When i took Carra's class, she was still a graduate student, teaching core and attempting at her dissertation simultaneously. (well, as i write this, she still is) You would have never know because she was so dedicated to her students. A little timid, but so intelligent and willing to help, she has been one of my favorite professors so far.

Carra is such a nice prof, she really cares about working with you to improve your writing skills both inside and outside of class. She made my very first college class experience a great one. She's awesome, highly recommended!

Carra is an awsome teacher. She has really helped  me with my writing because she takes the time to type out -sometimes a full page- of things you do well and things you can improve upon. She is friendly, funny, and genuine.

Carra is amazing.  She's easily my favorite teacher: brilliant, funny, enthusiastic, and ridiculously dedicated to her students.  She's a great listener and genuinely cares about her students' well-being (a rarity).  Folks who have the chance to cross classes, or paths, with Carra should consider themselves lucky.  Oh, and she's a stone cold fox.
